where n is the frequency index with nmax = [log(L/Ls)/logγ], D is the fractal dimension of the profile, G is a height-scaling parameter or the fractal roughness of the profile, γ determines the density of frequencies in the profile, M denotes the number of ridges required to reconstruct the profile and φn is a random phase.
